import React, { Component } from 'react' import axios from 'axios' export class Employee1 extends Component { constructor(props) { super(props) this.state = { list:[], popupbool:false, companyName:"", jobRole:"", location:"", experience:"", qualification:"", salary:"", link:"", id:"" } } componentDidMount(){ axios.get('http://localhost:3005/job-api') .then(res=>{this.setState({list:res.data})}) .catch() } render() { const {companyName,jobRole,location,experience,qualification,salary,link}=this.state return (




{this.state.list.map(x=>(<>

Company Name

{x.companyName}

Job Role

{x.jobRole}

Location

{x.location}

Experience

{x.experience}

Qualification

{x.qualification}

Salary

{x.salary}

Job link

link
))}
) } } export default Employee1
